<section class="section-faq">
  <div class="padding-global">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="padding-section-medium">
        <div class="faq-component">
          <div class="max-width _750 align-center">
            <div class="text-align-center">
              <div class="font-weight-bold"><h2 class="h-56">FAQ</h2></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="margin-top _64">
            <div class="faq-content">

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">01</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">Is Solly airplane-friendly?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">Yes. Solly features a 25,000mAh/ 92Wh battery, which is within the common carry-on limit for portable batteries. That makes it easy to bring in your cabin bag for flights, business trips, and everyday travel.</p></div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">02</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">Can it be used as a wall charger?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">Yes. Solly has a built-in wall plug, so you can plug it directly into a socket and use it like a charger while also recharging the power bank itself. No separate adapter is needed.</p></div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">03</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">Is it a travel adapter as well?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">Yes. Solly is designed to double as a travel adapter, making it more convenient for work trips, vacations, and everyday charging on the go.</p></div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">04</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">Can the lanyard be used as a charging cable?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">Yes. Solly includes a built-in USB-C to USB-C lanyard cable, so it is always ready when you need to charge without carrying an extra cable.</p></div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">05</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">What does solid-state battery mean?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">A solid-state battery uses a more advanced battery design focused on better safety, durability, and reliability compared to traditional battery systems. It is built to handle daily use more confidently and is designed to remain functional even under serious physical stress or damage.</p></div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">06</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">How long will the battery last?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">Solly uses an advanced battery system designed for long-term performance. The battery is built to retain over 80% of its performance even after 3 years of use, helping ensure reliable charging over time.</p></div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">07</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">Can Solly charge a laptop?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">Yes. Solly can easily charge laptops, including high-power devices, thanks to its 240W USB-C output.</p></div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">08</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">How fast does it charge devices?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">Very fast. Solly supports up to 240W fast charging through USB-C, making it powerful enough for laptops, tablets, phones, and other everyday devices.</p></div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">09</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">How long does it take to recharge the power bank itself?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">Solly can recharge itself in as little as 26 minutes to full charge, so it is ready again quickly when you need it.</p></div>
              </div>

              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">
                  <div class="font-question-text">
                    <div class="font-weight-light"><div class="faq-order">10</div></div>
                    <div class="font-weight-semibold"><div class="t-24">Does the solar panel really charge the power bank?</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="faq-icon"><div class="faq-icon-line"></div><div class="faq-icon-line is-vertical"></div></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer"><p class="faq-answer-text">Yes. Solly includes a built-in solar panel that can provide around 800mAh per hour in good sunlight. It is ideal for outdoor use, travel, and emergency backup charging when wall power is not available.</p></div>
              </div>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

